The paper deals with image recognition using deep neural networks, specifically pre-trained Inception ResNet models, and proposes a modified distribution alignment method for domain adaptation. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. Additionally, the paper involves feature extraction and classification, which are also relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the benchmark datasets used in the experiments are related to multimedia (cs.MM).
